  <div slot="quick-answer">
    <p><strong>Quick Answer:</strong> Choose Cabernet Sauvignon if you want more tannin, more structure, and a stronger fit for steak or aging. Choose Merlot if you want softer texture, easier drinkability, and a red that works better with weeknight food and less aggressive palates.</p>
  </div>

  <p>Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot come from the same Bordeaux family, but they solve different drinking problems. Cabernet is usually the answer when you want grip, darkness, and a more serious frame. Merlot is usually the answer when you want plush fruit, softer tannins, and a red that is easier to like young.</p>

